Introduction

Lee Daehwi is a South Korean singer-songwriter, dancer, composer, arranger, and actor under Brand New Music. He is best known as the lead vocalist, lead dancer, center, maknae, and face of the boy group AB6IX. He is also a former member of the project boy group Wanna One.

He is best known for being the center of the "It's Me (Pick Me)" evaluation during the survival show Produce 101 Season 2.

In 2017, Daehwi participated in the second season of Mnet's survival television show, Produce 101, along with four other trainees from his agency, Brand New Music. Him and Park Woo Jin were the only ones to make it to the final line-up, ranking 3rd and 6th, respectively, becoming members of the boy group Wanna One.

On August 7, 2017, he debuted in Wanna One with the mini album '1X1=1 (To Be One)' and its title track, "Energetic".

After the disbandment of Wanna One on January 27, 2019, Daehwi was revealed as a member of Brand New Music's new boy group, AB6IX, which consisted of all four trainees of Produce 101 and another trainee from the agency. The group debuted on May 22, 2019 with the mini album 'B:Complete' and its title track, "Breathe". Before their official debut, a performance video of the track "Hollywood" was released on April 25, 2019.
